   261→            <h2>Rotated Roots of Unity and Chebyshev Polynomials</h2>
   262→
   263→            <div class="badges">
   264→                <a href="https://github.com/e-vergo/ChebyshevCircles/actions/workflows/deploy.yml">
   265→                    <img src="https://github.com/e-vergo/ChebyshevCircles/actions/workflows/deploy.yml/badge.svg" alt="CI">
   266→                </a>
   267→                <a href="https://e-vergo.github.io/ChebyshevCircles/">
   268→                    <img src="https://github.com/e-vergo/ChebyshevCircles/actions/workflows/deploy.yml/badge.svg?label=docs" alt="Documentation">
   269→                </a>
   270→                <a href="LICENSE">
   271→                    <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Apache%202.0-blue.svg" alt="License">
   272→                </a>
   273→            </div>
   274→
   275→            <p>
   276→                Rotating the N-th roots of unity by angle φ and projecting them onto the real axis yields N points.
   277→                The polynomial with these projections as roots, when scaled by 2<sup>N-1</sup>, equals the N-th Chebyshev
   278→                polynomial of the first kind plus a constant that depends on φ.
   279→            </p>
   280→
   281→            <div class="theorem-box">
   282→                <h3>Main Theorem</h3>
   283→                <div class="theorem-statement">
   284→theorem rotated_roots_yield_chebyshev (N : ℕ) (φ : ℝ) (hN : 0 < N) :<br>
   285→&nbsp;&nbsp;∃ (c : ℝ), scaledPolynomial N φ = Polynomial.Chebyshev.T ℝ N + C c
   286→                </div>
   287→                <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
   288→                    <a href="./docs/ChebyshevCircles/MainTheorem.html#rotated_roots_yield_chebyshev" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500;">View theorem statement in API docs →</a>
   289→                </p>
   290→                <div class="construction">
   291→                    <strong>Construction:</strong>
   292→                    <ul>
   293→                        <li>Projected roots: <code>cos(φ + 2πk/N)</code> for k = 0, ..., N-1 <a href="./blueprint/sect0002.html" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem;">(blueprint §2)</a></li>
   294→                        <li>Unscaled polynomial: <code>P(x) = ∏(x - cos(φ + 2πk/N))</code> <a href="./blueprint/sect0003.html" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem;">(blueprint §3)</a></li>
   295→                        <li>Scaled polynomial: <code>S(x) = 2<sup>N-1</sup> · P(x)</code> <a href="./blueprint/sect0003.html" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem;">(blueprint §3)</a></li>
   296→                        <li>Result: <code>S(x) = T<sub>N</sub>(x) + c(φ)</code> <a href="./blueprint/sect0001.html" style="color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem;">(blueprint §1)</a></li>
   297→                    </ul>
   298→                </div>
   299→            </div>
